HEADWORD: Cassioberry
<hw>Cas"si*o*ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>cassine</ets>, from the language of the Florida Indians.]</ety>
<def>The fruit of the <spn>Viburnum obovatum</spn>, a shrub which grows
from Virginia to Florida.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

